headline: Leidos misses quarterly revenue estimates on government shutdown impact
summary: Feb 17 (Reuters) - Defense contractor Leidos Holdings reported fourth-quarter revenue below Wall Street estimates, as the six-week long U.S. government shutdown last year weighed on the firm's orders.
